A United States, US, Congresswoman, Ilhan Omar has called for President Donald Trump’s impeachment. Omar said she is “drawing up” articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump. She made the disclosure after the protest at Capitol building in Washington DC on Wednesday. “I am drawing up Articles of Impeachment,” the Democratic congresswoman wrote on her Twitter handle, NAN reports. “Donald J. Trump should be impeached by the House of Representatives and removed from office by the United States Senate,” she wrote. Hundreds of demonstrators breached security and scaled the steps of the building where lawmakers were due to certify president-elect Joe Biden’s win in the November election.